<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="1175" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1175">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">195.7 Richard Hovey/12–844:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Huddle</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-08">December 8,
                                        1944</date>.<lb/>[Received December 9—3:08 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>8041. American Interests—Japan. Legation’s 4029, June 23;<note n="53" xml:id="d1175fn53">See footnote 52, above.</note> Foreign Office
                                note December 7 states Swiss Legation in Tokyo telegraphs December 5
                                Japanese Foreign Office declared that thorough investigation
                                concerning torpedoing <hi rend="italic">Richard Hovey</hi> has been
                                made but revealed no action corresponding to that outlined in
                                Department’s 2043, June 14.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Huddle</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>